- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the effects of group development psychology training on agile software development teams. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the psychological perspective of small workgroups and their connection to team agility. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper touches on the potential positive effects of training on the entire software development organization. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper discusses the dynamics of small workgroups and their impact on team agility. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the least likely category as there is no mention of machine learning or any related techniques in the paper.
